social_posts.post_text: How many of us throw these things away? The Package Insert/prescribing information (PI) with all its technical jargon overwhelms a lot of people. Your pharmacist is an awesome person to ask about the PI! They do so much more than just fill your prescriptions. They can be a valuable addition to your asthma care team. Learn more here- this applies to all health conditions! https://www.cdc.gov/heartdisease/pharmacist.htm  #asthma #pharmacy #pharmacist #asthmaawareness #choosetobreathe

Knowing how and why you need a spacer can be confusing! A spacer is a holding chamber that attaches to your inhaler and using one will deliver the medication to your lungs more effectively. Here’s a great fact sheet from my friends @resphealth - https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Spacers-and-Metered-Dose-Inhalers_WYNTK.pdf  #asthma #asthmamanagement #spacers #inhaler #choosetobreathe #copd #copdawareness

Well, cold weather is here, and with that can come an increase in cold weather asthma symptoms! Learn more here- https://community.aafa.org/blog/cold-weather-advisory-people-with-asthma-should-take-precautions-to-avoid-symptoms  #asthma #asthmatic #asthmaproblems #choosetobreathe #coldweather

Let’s talk about Christmas trees and asthma! Real Christmas trees like cypress and pine can collect high amounts of pollen from other plants before they are cut down, which can trigger asthma and hay fever symptoms once you bring them home. Taking some precautions and working with your health care team can keep your holiday healthy! https://www.National asthma.org.au/news/2021/asthma-experts-warn-about-christmas-tree-syndrome  #asthmatic #asthma #allergies #christmastree #choosetobreathe

Happy first night of Hanukkah everyone! If you’re traveling to see family this holiday, here’s some #traveltips to keep you safe from #asthmatriggers this year! https://aafa.org/asthma/living-with-asthma/traveling-with-asthma-allergies/  #asthma #hannukah #asthmatips #holiday #holidaytravel

This is fascinating! I didn’t know that pointsettias are part of the rubber tree family and produce latex- if you are extra sensitive, this could be a problem for your asthma and allergies- make sure you check with your dr! https://allergyasthmanetwork.org/news/can-poinsettia-plants-cause-latex-allergy-reaction/ #pointsettia #asthma #asthmaproblems #allergies #latexallergy #choosetobreathe

With the winter weather is a rise in these respiratory viruses. People living with lung diseases can be more susceptible to severe illness if they contract one of these. Learn more about how to protect yourself at this link from @resphealth here! https://resphealth.org/copd-and-lung-viruses/?fbclid=IwAR1UrwyyCj79HbcIwwAkGyBkgQSoTErH-BkRplQ8VRy-dMVwOdprYh5DXAc  #christmas #rsv #flu #hannukah #thegrinch #asthma #copd #choosetobreathe

It’s below zero here in Chicago! Be extra vigilant about symptoms of cold weather asthma, carry your inhaler and check with your doctor if you need to! Here’s some tips for #coldweatherasthma from a reputable source- https://www.allergyinstitute.org/blog/winter-asthma-five-ways-to-avoid-asthma-attacks-during-cold-weather #choosetobreathe #asthma #allergies #asthmaproblems #copd #coldweather

Finishing up this #holidayseries of #asthmatips talking about pets and traveling with some help from my own kitty, Treble! Always consult your health care professional team to manage your meds and traveling! (Ps- I am not allergic to Trebs so he doesn’t flare my asthma!) https://acaai.org/news/expert-tips-for-managing-asthma-and-allergies-during-the-holidays/ #choosetobreathe #asthma #pets #blackcatsofinstagram #asthmaproblems #allergies #copd

Sounds like a great #newyearsresolution to me! Here’s some tips on how to clean your #asthma or #copd #inhaler #spacer ! (Read this! https://allergyasthmanetwork.org/news/why-and-how-wash-your-valved-holding-chamber/ )
#choosetobreathe #asthmaproblems #copd #asthmaawareness #copdawareness

It’s a new year and that’s a great time to check and see if you need any refills! Here’s some reasons why it’s important to refill your inhaler ahead of time! (https://asthma.net/living/watch-your-inhaler-counters) #asthma #copd #inhaler #refill #choosetobreathe

Just take the inhaler. I get it. It’s a pain, its embarrassing, maybe you’re super into that viewing of #glassonionaknivesoutmystery , whatever. Not taking it can mean bigger problems later. (https://kidshealth.org/en/parents/no-asthma-medication.html)  #asthma #asthmaattacks #asthmamanagement #copd #inhaler #choosetobreathe

It can be hard to find the expiration date on your #inhalers! Check the metal canister inside the plastic dispenser- and also the prescription label stuck to the box if you hang on to it! #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmaproblems #copd #asthmatips #asthmatipsandtricks #healthylungs

No articles today on inhaler effectiveness-
just this simple message. The truth is my inhaler keeps me alive. There’s no shame in needing it. Take your inhaler. #choosetobreathe #asthma #copd #inhaler #asthmaproblems #asthmatips
Taking your meds (and not just inhalers- this can go for any meds) isn’t a ‘hot take.’ It’s just common sense! #choosetobreathe #asthma #copd #chronicdisease #inhaler #medicationmanagement

It’s so important to me to get this point across that I’m willing to dance ridiculously for the entire internet to see. #asthma isn’t a weakness, it can be manageable with consistent treatment and working with your health care team! #chronicillness #copd #asthmatips #choosetobreathe #pharmacist #lunghealth

Patients with good inhaler techniques and compliance have better control of their asthma. That means 1) learn the right way to use it and 2) use it when you need it! @resphealth fact sheets are an excellent place to start! https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Asthma-Quick-Facts.pdf  #asthma #asthmaproblems #choosetobreathe #inhaler #inhalerlife

It’s been awhile since I posted an #inhaler #quicktip since they generally get very low view counts because they aren’t as fun to watch, but this info is important so I’m bringing them back! Learn more about spacers here at this @resphealth fact sheet! https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Spacers-and-Metered-Dose-Inhalers_WYNTK.pdf  #asthma #asthmamanagement #copd #copdawareness #choosetobreathe

There is ZERO shame in needing help to breathe. But the truth is, most teens won’t take their life saving inhaler in front of others even if they are having a serious attack. I want to normalize inhaler use. I #choosetobreathe . (SOURCE https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5734261/) #asthma #asthmaproblems #copd #copdawareness #inhaler #chronicillness #swiftie

Facts are facts. These are from the CDC- About 10 people each day die from asthma, and 25+ million Americans have it- that amounts to $56 billions spent on direct costs (to doctors, hospitals, medications) and indirect costs (lost work and school.) CDC #asthma data here- https://www.cdc.gov/asthma/most_recent_national_asthma_data.htm  #lunghealth #choosetobreathe #asthmamyths

Get to know our friend @miarosefa_choosetobreathe!!

Mia is a longtime supporter of Mobile Care Chicago, and an asthma advocate through her own social media platforms, helping to inform people with asthma about the chronic health condition. She creates engaging and creative content to help other teens and children feel understood and educated instead of feeling embarrassed about their illness. 

We admire the great work Mia continues to do to help make asthma education fun and exciting! To learn more about the person responsible for the great content, read our interview with Mia through the link in our bio!

#freehealthcare #asthma #asthmaeducation #influencer #chicagononprofits #nonprofit #nonprofitorganization #chicago #respiratory

Like any #chronicillness just because your #asthma is feeling better doesn’t mean it’s gone or you should stop taking your meds. It probably means those meds are doing their job! ALWAYS check with your doctor or pharmacist if you feel like stopping your #inhaler because you feel better. (https://www.chop.edu/news/asthma-myths-and-facts) #choosetobreathe #asthmamanagement #asthmaproblems #copd #copdsucks #asthmasucks #healthylungs

Do certain fragrances and strong odors seem to make your asthma worse? If so, you’re not alone. For some people, strong odors from perfumes, household or industrial cleaners, air fresheners, and nail polishes and removers can trigger asthma symptoms. Luckily, my beloved ‘Leaves’ candle doesn’t set me off. Work with your doc to learn your #asthma triggers! (https://www.asthma.com/understanding-asthma/asthma-triggers/strong-odors-and-asthma/) #choosetobreathe #asthmaproblems #asthmatriggers #inhaler

Like that #inhaler spacer, you need to clean your neb! It can get super gross and no one wants to inhale bacteria back into their lungs! https://www.lung.org/lung-health-diseases/lung-disease-lookup/copd/patient-resources-and-videos/how-to-clean-a-nebulizer  #asthmamanagement #asthma #choosetobreathe #copd #nebulizer
The 25 million Americans with asthma would disagree… (https://www.cdc.gov/asthma/nchs.html) #choosetobreathe #asthma #chronicillness #cdcstats #asthmaproblems

Everyone’s asthma is different, so work with your doctor need to create an asthma treatment plan that’s best for you. Following your treatment plan is the best bet for controlling asthma! (https://aafa.org/asthma/asthma-treatment/) #asthma #asthmaproblems #asthmaawareness #choosetobreathe

Can cold air affect your asthma? Some #asthmatics are more susceptible in winter to the dry, cold air, which makes it hard to breathe. Fortunately, there are ways to deal with this by working with your health care team and following your #asthmaactionplan , having your inhaler on hand, and choosing indoor activities. More info here! https://community.aafa.org/blog/cold-weather-advisory-people-with-asthma-should-take-precautions-to-avoid-symptoms #asthmamanagement #choosetobreathe #asthmatips #asthmasucks #copd #lunghealth

Yes, I spend ALOT of time talking about why you should take your inhaler when you need it. But that’s because most teens won’t, because they are embarrassed. I get it, I’ve been there. I have had to haul my neb to dance more times than I can count. There’s no shame in needing help to breathe- it’s no reflection on who you are as a person! AND- if you need extra help on HOW to properly take it, here’s a great #asthma #factsheet from my friends @resphealth ! https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Spacers-and-Metered-Dose-Inhalers_WYNTK.pdf  #asthmamanagement #asthmatips #copd #lunghealth #choosetobreathe

It’s me. Hi. I’m the problem, it’s me.  Calling myself out publicly should make me wash this right? Yes, you should wash your spacer once a week in warm soapy water. Watch for a follow up tomorrow!  Cleaning instructions at this @resphealth fact sheet on spacers here-  https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Spacers.pdf  #asthma #inhalers #asthmaproblems #asthmatips #copd #choosetobreathe

Since I called myself out yesterday, I had to fix the situation, so let’s wash my spacer. Instructions for how to do this from my friends @resphealth here- https://resphealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Spacers.pdf

Everyone gets confused on this sometimes! Both #asthmatics and people with #copd may rely on multiple inhalers for breathing. Your doctor, nurse, and pharmacist are great sources of help, and so is this #factsheet from my friends @resphealth here- https://resphealth.org/news/library/asthma-medications/  #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmaawareness #asthmamanagement #copdawareness

It’s been awhile since I’ve brought out my inner Moira Rose!  Here’s a few common #asthmatriggers #schittscreek style! (Read about #asthma triggers here https://www.cdc.gov/asthma/triggers.html ) #choosetobreathe #asthmamanagement

If anyone (other than your health care provider) tells you your dog automatically has to go if you have asthma, that can be a red flag. Work with your doctor on allergy testing and a treatment plan and it might not be necessary. I get allergy tested regularly and my dog doesn’t set off my allergies or asthma so I can have her in my home. Thanks to Chua my chiweenie for being my adorable co-star! (https://asthma.net/living/can-i-still-have-a-dog) #choosetobreathe #asthma #allergies #asthmaproblems #asthmatips #treatmentplan #chiweeniesofinstagram

I’m not being sarcastic- this really is fun! When I hear someone say “seeing your reel/Tiktok reminded me to take my inhaler,” it’s gratifying to know I’m making a small difference. #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmatic #inhaler

Just a simple message today- always check your counter and make sure you order your refill before the counter is in the red zone! Work with your pharmacist to help get your refills in time. #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmatips #pharmacist #inhaler

This trend… 120 million Americans live with chronic illness- that’s a whole lot of us isn’t it? #iwasbornintherightgeneration (https://www.aafp.org/pubs/afp/issues/2005/1015/p1503.html#:~:text=Approximately%20120%20million%20Americans%20have%20one%20or%20more%20chronic%20illnesses%2C%20accounting%20for%2070%20to%2080%20percent%20of%20health%20care%20costs.) #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmaawareness #copd #copdawareness #chronicillness
That’s it. That’s the message today. Take your meds when you need them, especially if you need your inhaler, to keep staying healthy! #choosetobreathe #asthma #copd #inhaler

Advocacy for #lunghealth can start with a few clicks! Don’t know who your elected officials are? Hey everybody! I’m heading to college next year- so now is the perfect time for a series on how to prepare for college with asthma. Part 1- and step 1 will be about allergy testing. My allergist (who is awesome btw) suggested we start the prep by seeing if I have had any changes to what I react to as my asthma is very allergy driven. Come along with me for my allergy tests! @resphealth #asthma #allergies #goingtocollege #cleanair #healthylungs #choosetobreathe

It’s Easter and Passover week- here’s a few tips to keep in mind for your #asthmatic guests and #copd guests who celebrate! #easter #passover #asthma #copd #healthylungs #choosetobreathe (https://community.aafa.org/blog/3-ways-to-keep-spring-celebrations-asthma-and-allergy-friendly)

#allergytesting for Part 2 of the series ‘preping for college with asthma! ‘ If you’ve never been allergy tested- here’s a very up close look at the process. TW if scratches or red itchy skin bothers you. It honestly looks worse than it feels to have it done! #asthma #allergies #scratchtest #choosetobreathe

Since almost half of kids with asthma can also have food allergies, I thought it would be great to focus on the food allergy that is a big danger during both #easter and #passover- eggs! Here’s some tips for my #asthmatic friends with egg allergies who celebrate either. And ALWAYS check with your doctor for what’s best for your personal situation. (Severely allergic people may have a reaction from contact alone so know your personal triggers.) (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6780261/) #easter #passover #passoverseder #choosetobreathe #eggallergy #foodallergies #asthma

Happy Easter if you celebrate! Guess Trebbie was not too happy subbing in for the Easter Bunny in my reel! Nevertheless, here’s the most common #spring #asthma #triggers to look out for- carry your rescue inhaler and update your #asthmacareplan ! (https://www.pennmedicine.org/updates/blogs/health-and-wellness/2017/april/asthma)#choosetobreathe #asthmaproblems #copd #inhaler

I had a wonderful night at the @ncwitaic regional awards banquet. @ncwit stands for the National Center for Women & Information Technology. This amazing org works to increase the participation of all women in computing—at the intersections of race/ethnicity, class, age, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability status, and other historically marginalized identities. I am honored to be a regional Aspirations in Computing awardee. Even more fun was seeing Eden @eden.ishh @lemonerdy who you might recognize as our forever @misshydeparkot ! @misschicagoil @missillinoisorganization

Since this audio is trending again- yes, #truestory I have been asked this before. #asthmatics do get comments like this. I try to take it as an opportunity to educate and normalize #asthma. #copd #inhaler #choosetobreathe #chronicillness

There is currently no cure for #asthma . (And it’s definitely not lemons, onions, etc.) Fortunately, most asthma can be managed and controlled with proper medication and education. That is why it’s so important to work with your dr. and follow your treatment plan! (SOURCE https://resphealth.org/healthy-lungs/asthma/understanding-asthma/) #asthmaproblems #asthmamanagement #inhaler #choosetobreathe #chronicillness

@jtv is supporting @resphealth Respiratory Health Association’s “Catch Your Breath” campaign again this May! In honor of that, enjoy this PSA I shot in 2019 in support of this wonderful campaign I love supporting. (I cannot believe how little I sound!) Now through May 25th, proceeds from the sales of gorgeous butterfly jewelry goes to support #catchyourbreath women’s lung research and programs. Stay tuned for my unboxing of my butterfly this year to support @resphealth !  Link here- https://www.jtv.com/about/cares/catch-your-breath?mcid=XSOInstagram0002892

For the past 3 years I’ve been a part of an amazing program for high school students interested in pursuing a career in engineering, architecture or construction called ACE Chicago. I am very excited to share that because of this program I was hired to work as an intern this summer at Chicago engineering firm AECOM- I will be working directly on a job site at the water reclamation plant and getting lots of hands on mechanical and environmental engineering experience!

Wow, what a day! I am so honored to have this experience and award as a Prudential Emerging Visionary, and am so energized to grow #choosetobreathe and reach so many more people with Prudential’s support!

I had an amazing time @pruemergingvisionaries but now it’s back to business as usual here at #choosetobreathe - let’s normalize #chronicillness and using medical devices. There is no shame in needing a little extra help to breathe or anything else! #asthma #inhaler #healthylungs #copd #asthmaawareness #asthmaprobs

Best feeling ever hearing that even one person didn’t give it a second thought to pull out their inhaler when they needed it. Let’s keep doing that! #asthma #asthmamanagement #inhaler #choosetobreathe #copd #johncena #johncenameme

It’s #worldasthmaday and I know navigating all the #asthma info out there (some of it false and harmful!) on the internet can be really confusing for #asthmatics. Your Dr. and Pharmacist are great places to start! And online, stick to professional health organizations who have their content written and reviewed by trusted health professionals like my fave, @resphealth - you can always visit their asthma fact sheets and more at resphealth.org! #choosetobreathe #healthylungs #inhaler

Welcome back spring asthma symptoms- can’t say I missed you! For those of us with #allergicasthma spring can be rough- know the symptoms of #spring #asthma ! (https://www.lung.org/blog/dont-fear-spring-allergies) #asthmaproblems #choosetobreathe #springallergies #inhaler

Stop believing stupid people. The latest numbers from @cdcgov tell us 25 MILLION of us have #asthma and 10 of us still die every day. Work with your dr. and pharmacist for a treatment plan and take your #inhaler when you need it! (https://www.cdc.gov/asthma/most_recent_national_asthma_data.htm) #choosetobreathe #asthmamanagement #asthmaproblems
I have this thing… my #inhaler helps me be able to do all this! #choosetobreathe #asthma #asthmamanagement #copd

Did you know it is #nationalskillednursingcareweek? Thanks to @lindseynhess I do- this week celebrates the essential role that skilled nursing care centers play in providing 24-hour nursing care to millions of America’s seniors and individuals with disabilities, including my Grandpa John. Chances are you love someone who has been in long term care too, make sure you thank their nurse for all they do! #nsncw #nsncw2023

Six out of every 10 Americans deal with one or more chronic illnesses like lung diseases such as #asthma and #copd, #inflammatoryboweldisease , #heartdisease, #diabetes , #als , #kidneydisease , #eatingdisorders , #arthritis and more. These are just a few. The truth is we’re in the majority and there’s no need to be embarrassed. The more we talk about it the more normalized it becomes. (Source CDC - https://www.cdc.gov/chronicdisease/resources/infographic/chronic-diseases.htm)

The discovery of #albuterol and the invention of portable, lightweight disposable #inhalers changed the game for asthmatics living their everyday lives. Here’s a carousel about the scientists involved! (Apparently carousels are the new reels, so let’s see how this does. Am I going to stop making reels? I doubt it. But I’ll feed the algorithm today.) #sciencesaves #choosetobreathe #asthma
Take your daily inhaler EVERY DAY so it can be most effective! #choosetobreathe #asthma #inhaler #corticosteroids

Who else can go from feeling perfectly great to a full on #asthma attack? That’s why it’s important to take your meds and follow your #asthmaactionplan from your doctor even if you feel fine! #pedropascal #hotones #asthmamanagement #asthmaproblems #choosetobreathe #copd #inhaler
Here’s your reminder to contact your #pharmacist and refill that rescue #albuterol #inhaler so it’s there when you need it! #asthma #choosetobreathe #copd #refill

Airnow.gov is a great resource to check the air quality of where you live! Every summer poor air quality kicks off #airqualityactiondays here in Chicago, and it’s started early because the fires in Canada made it all the way here, and even further! An #airqualityactionday mean it’s not safe for people with lung diseases and other immuno-compromised people to exercise or spend a lot of time outside. Check your air quality! #choosetobreathe #asthmamanagement #copd #lunghealth #airquality @epagov
I think I’ll skip the onion syrup recipes and just keep taking my meds. (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19945775/) #choosetobreathe #asthmamyths #asthma

Nice summer weather means more time outside and potentially more exposure to #asthma triggers- always carry your rescue #inhaler and stick to your #asthmaactionplan (https://www.lung.org/blog/asthma-in-the-summer) #choosetobreathe #asthmamanagement
Coming at you with some common #asthmatriggers and a favorite audio from #hamiltonmusical ! #choosetobreathe #asthma #inhaler

#sponsored I’m going to be honest, asthma isn’t cute. Like all teens, I love fashion and looking my best, but the truth is that living with asthma can really look like how you see me here. On this page, I don’t use filters or retouching because I want to be honest with my followers about what asthma struggles are like. Not everything I carry with me on-the-go is cute but it represents what people with asthma may deal with, especially during #AsthmaPeakWeek and the transition to the fall season when asthma attacks increase. The reality is that people with asthma struggle with triggers like ragweed, mold, and poor air quality. For me, asthma flare-ups can cause missed days at work and school, and emergency room visits. This is why I always carry my rescue inhaler and use as needed to quickly relieve my symptoms when they occur.
As an #AstraZenecaPartner, I encourage you to visit the link in my bio to learn about the #2sides2asthma, airway tightening and airway inflammation, and talk to your doctor about asthma and treatment options that may be appropriate for you. @astrazeneca

#sponsored Asthma Peak Week occurred in the third week in September and marked the transition to the fall season. This time of year can be scary for many people with asthma due to the rise in asthma attacks, but it can make it a little easier to get through when you have a plan with your doctor! In partnership with AstraZeneca, I’m here to share about the #2sides2asthma: airway tightening and airway inflammation. Both can contribute to asthma symptoms like shortness of breath, chest tightness, wheezing, and coughing. As a part of my own plan, I always carry my rescue inhaler with me in case I need it to quickly relieve my asthma symptoms when they occur. Although there are 2 sides 2 an asthma flare-up, current rescue inhalers may not treat airway inflammation. Visit the link in my bio to learn about the 2 sides 2 asthma and talk to your doctor about asthma and treatment options that may be appropriate for you. #AstraZenecaPartner @astrazeneca

Have you heard of the #thanksgivingeffect with #asthma - this phenomenon occurs when a person loses tolerance to her own pet after being away for a few days. It doesn’t mean you can’t have your pet, just be extra aware and work with your doctor and pharmacist for the best way to handle it! (https://www.aaaai.org/tools-for-the-public/conditions-library/asthma/allergies,-asthma-and-winter-holidays#:~:text=If%20you%20leave%20your%20pet,away%20for%20a%20few%20days.&text=Be%20aware%20that%20stress%20can%20lead%20to%20asthma%20attacks.) #turkeyday #thanksgiving #asthma #choosetobreathe
